<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-358-432  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 358 432.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic News  April 16 1990 v36 n1805 p4(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Communications firms clash on industry's infrastructure. (regionalBell operating companies and equipment manufacturers)andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Regional Bell operating companies (RBOC) are in disagreement withequipment manufacturers over the health of the telecommunicationsindustry, after the Commerce Department asked for input on thegovernment's role in shaping the nation's telecommunicationsfuture infrastructure.andP;  The RBOCs complain that the industry isfalling behind, due to government regulation, while manufacturerscontend that the industry is still in the lead.andP;  The RBOCs citeproof from a study by Management Education Services Associatesthat reveals the US telecommunications industry, when comparedwith other nation, is behind in key areas such as networkdigitalization, integrated systems digital networks and CCS7deployment, and key services, including videotex gateways andother information services.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Management Education Services Associates (reports).andO;Topic:     Bell Regional Holding CompaniesDeregulationGovernment RegulationInformation servicesISDNCompetitionStudyLeadershipTelecommunicationsUnited States. Department of CommerceTelephone companiesCommunications Equipment.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>